   That is kinda ironic isn't it? Actually, the fixpack 12 
   
   has not been officially released so it hasn't been tested 
   
   for problems w/ all systems. Here's a quick rundown on the 
   
   fixpacks. 
   
   1) Joe Blow has a problem with Warp and calls IBM tech. 
   
   2) IBM either tells him where the patch is or writes one 
   
   for him. 
   
   3) IBM collects these "fixes" into fixpacks. (BTW, 
   
   fixpacks are made up of "fixes" that have no other patch) 
   
   4) Next guy calls with the same problem as Joe Blow. 
   
   5) IBM sends him a copy of the fixpack instead of writing a 
   
   fix again. 
   
   6) After a fixpack has been tested enough, it is released 
   
   to the public. 
   
